Get g2ipmsg working in Kubuntu

# Introduction

g2ipmsg gives some encryption related errors when used with normal Windows
clients. To disable encryption in the g2ipmsg package use these steps:

{{{sh
sudo aptitude install dpkg-dev debhelper devscripts fakeroot linda
apt-get source g2ipmsg
cd g2ipmsg-0.9.6+dfsg
echo "DEB_CONFIGURE_EXTRA_FLAGS = --without-ssl" >> debian/rules
dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot
sudo dpkg -i g2ipmsg_0.9.6+dfsg-1_i386.deb
}}}

To stop apt-get/aptitude from trying to upgrade your custom deb with the
default package we can use this command:

{{{sh
echo "g2ipmsg hold" | sudo dpkg --set-selections
}}}

This method fixes you deb file forever. If you want to keep your deb file but
still let apt-get/aptitude notify you  if there is a newer official version of the
deb package you must add an entry to the debian/changelog file making sure to
slightly modify the version information:

{{{debchangelog
g2ipmsg (0.9.6+dfsg-1-nossl) unstable; urgency=low

  * Disable ssl encryption schemes.

 -- Horacio Sanson <horacio@skillupjapan.co.jp>  Wed, 29 Sep 2010 16:33:00 +0900

g2ipmsg (0.9.6+dfsg-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release (Closes: #551615)

 -- TANIGUCHI Takaki <takaki@debian.org>  Tue, 20 Oct 2009 13:26:50 +0900
}}}

